name: ENGINE BUZZ! Air Canada A321-211 [C-GITU] Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
First time flying on a Star Alliance bird! Here we have Air Canada's Star Alliance A321 taxiing and taking off from Calgary International Airport at around 8AM, with some incredible engine sound! Sorry about the kid talking, but it wouldn't be a true inflight video without one. Listen to the awesome change in sound at 6:55 as the pilots set the engines to cruise power. See the video log below for more. Enjoy!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

VIDEO LOG:
00:11 - The aircraft parked at YYC.
00:26 - Pushing back.
02:04 - Starting taxi.
05:09 - Spooling up (If you're short on time, watch from here).
06:50 - Climb power set.
09:03 - Banking east.
09:50 - A view of YYC.
